claim.text: Meta Agent Search can discover agents that outperform state-of-the-art hand-designed agents across multiple domains
claim.exact_quote: The results across multiple domains demonstrate that Meta Agent Search can discover agents that outperform state-of-the-art hand-designed agents.

evidence.evidence_text: Improvements in F1 scores by 13.6/100 and accuracy rates by 14.4% in the Reading Comprehension and Math domains, respectively.
evidence.limitations: The improvement is domain-specific with larger gaps in ones where FMs possess adequate knowledge.
evidence.exact_quote: We want to highlight the substantial gap between the learned agents and hand-designed agents in the Reading Comprehension and Math domains, with improvements in F1 scores by 13.6/100 and accuracy rates by 14.4%, respectively.

evaluation.justification: The evidence strongly supports the claim in specific domains, showing substantial improvements over hand-designed baselines.
evaluation.key_limitations: The effectiveness of Meta Agent Search varies across domains, with the smallest performance gaps witnessed in more challenging domains with insufficient FM knowledge.

claim.text: Discovered agents exhibit robustness and transferability across domains
claim.exact_quote: Our agents improve accuracy by 25.9% on GSM8K and 13.2% on GSM-Hard compared to the baselines when transferring within math domains.

evidence.evidence_text: Notable improvements in transferred agent performances within math domains (25.9% on GSM8K and 13.2% on GSM-Hard).
evidence.limitations: Transferability performance drop when applied to non-match domains; still outperforms the baseline but indicates domain-specific optimization.
evidence.exact_quote: Our agents improve accuracy by 25.9% on GSM8K and 13.2% on GSM-Hard compared to the baselines when transferring within math domains.

evaluation.justification: Evidence indicates a significant performance increase when agents discovered in math domains are transferred to other math domains and even to non-math domains, though with some performance decrease.
evaluation.key_limitations: Some performance decrease when transferring agents to non-math domains, suggesting specialization in the training domain.

claim.text: Meta Agent Search utilizes a growing archive of previous designs to innovate, demonstrating a significant potential of ADAS for discovering novel design patterns and agentic systems
claim.exact_quote: Meta Agent Search innovates based on a growing archive of previous stepping stones... This illustrates that even though these stepping stones did not achieve high performance immediately upon emergence, later discoveries benefited from these innovations.

evidence.evidence_text: An iterative process of innovation was observed, with newer agents benefitting from emergent design patterns and essential stepping stones from a growing archive.
evidence.limitations: Lacks specificity on the quantitative impact of these innovations on agent performance.
evidence.exact_quote: This illustrates that even though these stepping stones did not achieve high performance immediately upon emergence, later discoveries benefited from these innovations by combining different stepping stones.

evaluation.justification: The claim is justified by the qualitative analysis of the innovation process; however, quantitative impact on performance is not directly linked.
evaluation.key_limitations: The methodology's effectiveness in qualitative terms is evident, but the lack of direct quantitative evidence on improved performance for individual stepping stones remains a limitation.
